// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Contact Name : Pit 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Name :
"P1890226793" "Pit"
// LocationString :
// ProfessionString :
// CallTextOverride :
// AskAboutTextOverride :
// ContactRequiresText :
// FailsafeLevelString :

// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Dialog - DialogTree 
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
// Page Intro Text :
"P2642365905" "Hey, what's up?  A little bird told me that you've got yourself some troubles.  The name's Pit - as in that thing you bite into when chompin' on a cherry.  You know what I'm talking about - really good lookin' on the outside, nice and sweet on the inside, and then it's all - 'Oh noes!  I just busted all my teeth on this Pit here!'.  Now... your face is telling me that you've got questions about tracking down <color orange>Tips</color> - no... maybe it's about how you <color orange>Align</color> yourself?  Hmm... nah... maybe it's about your <color orange>Supergroup</color> dudes and girlies, right?  Tell you the truth, I can't really tell with the way your face is all scrunched up like that.  How's about you just ask me already, cool?"
// Answer Text :
// Answer Text :
// Answer Text :
// Answer Text :
// Page IntroReturn Text :
"P1498852791" "Hey, whatever.  It's not like I've got, oh you know, kittens to rescue from trees and OLD LADIES TO WALK ACROSS STREETS AND ALL!<br><br>Wait.<br><br>Hmm... yeah I guess I don't.  So what's up?"
// Page TipsMain Text :
"P2029949476" ""So look... as you run around swattin' things while going 'Hey, look at me!  I'm SuperCool {hero.gender= male Dude|Chick}!", you're gonna come across things that give you ideas.  I like to call them... Tips.  Well, so do a lot of other people, I guess.  But hey, whatever.<br><br>These ideas you come across will let you really show off what kinda person you really are.  You know, like the way your mom used to tell you that you were 'special'.<br><br>Yeah.  Like that.<br><br><color orange>Tips drop from many enemies throughout the game.  You can locate the tips you have found in the Tips tab in the Contact window.  Click on Investigate to begin a Tip Mission.</color>"
// Answer Text :
// Answer Text :
// Answer Text :
"P3726443615" "How many Tips do I get to do?"
// Answer Text :
// Page TipsMainReturn Text :
"P1684441719" "Snap snap, little puppy! If you've gotta question, you'd best just - heh - 'Spit' it out already!  Ha!  Gotta remember that one.  So look - I've got things do, places to go, people to beat!  Those banks ain't gonna rob themselves, you know what I'm sayin'?"
// Answer Text :
// Page TipsExplanation Text :
"P3151645680" "So when you come up with a Tip, it's all up to you on how you want to take a stab at it.  Who knows, maybe that's the way you want to do a Tip - stab at it with, like, a big knife.  Or maybe you wanna just grab the cash and run.  Or heck... maybe you're all into doing the right thing and wanna, I don't know, save some innocent lives or that kinda thing.<br><br>Heeyyyy... I'm not judging.  Really!  I'm not!  Okay, yeah I am.<br><br>Anyways, the point is that you can do things your own way for as long as you like until, well, you gotta get off the pot and really make a choice by doing a Morality Mission.<br><br>And seriously? I'm judging.  Mmmhmmm.<br><br><color orange>To begin a Tip Mission, click on the Investigate button.  When choosing an Alignment path, you will be given an option to commit to that Alignment's version of the mission or to reconsider.  Once you have committed your choice, you will not be able to do the other Alignment's version unless you acquire that Tip again.</color>"
// Answer Text :
"P4010687976" "What is a Morality Mission?"
// Answer Text :
// Page TipsMorality Text :
"P4037561454" "I'd think the name would have given it away, but hey, whatever.  So once you've made a name for yourself by doing <b>TEN</b> 'lil things that people get talking about, that's when you can pull the big job.  That super-big one gets your name in the book, or history books, depending on how you look at it.  Once you go through with that one, there ain't no goin' back.  EVERYONE will know you for what you truly, truly are...<br><br><color orange>Completing a Tip will award you with a point in the mission's Alignment.  After gaining 10 points in one alignment, you will be given a Morality Mission.  Taking and completing that mission will change your Alignment to the type for that Morality Mission.<br><br>If more than one team member are eligible to change to that alignment, the accompanying teammate(s) will be given the choice to change alignments.  If no one else is eligible to change alignments, they will still be given a point in the alignment.</color>"
// Page TipsPerDay Text :
"P881144964" "Do however many you want, {Hero.gender=Male bro|girlie}!  Go off and beat dudes silly, trick the authorities into handing over their cash, or heck, even do guard duty for long-haired hippies while they protest their bleeding hearts out.  Really? I don't care.<br><br>But 'people', you see... they've got the attention span of a gnat.  If you do any more than <b>FIVE</b> in a given day, they totally forget about all the dang other things you did!!!<br><br><color orange>The first <b>FIVE</b> Tips will award points towards your Morality Meter.  24 hours after you have completed the Tip, you will be given the opportunity to gain another point towards your totals.</color>"
// Answer Text :
// Page AlignmentMain Text :
"P844880957" "There are a bunch of different ways to look at this world, you know? It's not all black and white, all heroes and villains and all that junk.  There are shades of grey in between all of that.  For every dude out there who kills himself to save everyone else, there's another guy who's willing to kill others for that same goal.<br><br>And just because some dude out there wants to be the prince of this world doesn't mean there isn't a guy who just wants a bag of silver.  Or even better... a huge sack of cash.<br><br><color orange>The Alignment System will allow your character to become one of four different alignments - Hero, Vigilante, Villain, or Rogue.  Characters will automatically begin as either a Hero or a Villain when first entering Primal Earth.</color>"
// Answer Text :
// Answer Text :
"P55992386" "What happens if I change alignments?"
// Answer Text :
// Answer Text :
// Answer Text :
// Page AlignmentCycle Text :
"P2256655106" "If you wanna make a change in your life, follow those Tips to the pot of gold at the end, you know what I'm saying?  A Hero may get fed up with that one boogeyman always breaking out of prison and decide to solve the problem once and for all as a Vigilante.  Or a Vigilante realizing that light at the end of the Tunnel o' Justice is actually a train may turn around and do it the safe Hero way.<br><br>Villains could get smart and leave all the power-grabbing to suckers, living on Easy Street as a Rogue.  And a Rogue may get tired of being kicked around and start doing the kicking themselves as a Villain.<br><br>Then again, a Vigilante can always take it a step too far when they realize that murder, well, it's illegal from what I hear.  BAM!!!  Villain.  Or, who knows... a Rogue can kick the history professors in the yoozies and show them they've been the biggest Hero of that story the whole time.  Crazier things can happen, you know?<br><br><color orange>A Hero may stay being a Hero or become a Vigilante, and vice versa.  A Villain may stay being a Villain or become a Rogue, and vice versa.<br><br>A Vigilante may become a Villain, but must become a Rogue and then a Hero to be eligible to become a Vigilante again.  A Rogue may become a Hero, but must become a Vigilante and then a Villain to be eligible to become a Rogue again.</color>"
// Answer Text :
// Page AlignmentChanges Text :
"P1289595387" "Well, that's when everything changes for you.  You get a brand new lease on life, I guess.  All that stuff you did before gets totally ignored, since everyone only cares about the here and now.  And watch it... your old friends are gonna be like "You! You suck now, you rotten eggsucking, eggsucker...uh... punk!" and other things I don't want offend your delicate little ears with.<br><br>Oh yeah... the same goes with all those other ideas you had, those Tips.  Total garbage at that point.  I mean, why would you want to stop a busload of kittens being driven by nuns from falling into a lake of radioactive snakes anymore?  Unless that's your thing, that is... and hey, whatever floats your boat.  Or your busload of kittens in this case.<br><br><color orange>Upon completing a Morality Mission that changes your alignment, all Morality Points will be reset and all remaining Tips will be removed.  If you have changed from a Vigilante to a Villain, you will no longer be allowed in Paragon City.  If you have changed from a Rogue to a Hero, you will no longer be allowed in the Rogue Isles.</color>"
// Page AlignmentRewards Text :
// Answer Text :
// Page SupergroupMain Text :
"P1161470793" "Supergroups?  Oh, you mean all those groups of people going 'For Freedom!' or 'Smash Everything!' or 'Please Don't Kill Us!'?  What happens to those dudes?  Nothin'.<br><br>I mean, Heroes and Vigilantes are still chillin' with each other, and Villains and Rogues still hang out doing the same thing they do every night.  Just don't go confusing your buddies.  You can't get the leader of all your buddies killed and expect said buddies to be, well, all buddy-buddy with you anymore.  I mean, c'mon... let's get real here.  Heroes and Villains mix together like water to - uh - oil.<br><br><color orange>Characters who switch sides by becoming a Villain or a Hero will not be removed from their supergroup, but will no longer be able to access various benefits granted to a Hero/Villain supergroup."
// Answer Text :
// Answer Text :
// Answer Text :
// Answer Text :
// Answer Text :
// Page SupergroupExclusion Text :
"P2029367327" "You gotta be kiddin' me!  Can you still go into your Supergroup's Base?  Dude... would you invite over for dinner the dude who just doublecrossed you several days ago?  Or open the door to a guy you know is just going to set all your captives free?  Sheesh.<br><br>So no.  You can't.  Heck, deep down inside you may be the biggest saint among all your friends, or the most deceptive of your dear dastardly denizens, but that doesn't matter a whit.  They ain't lettin' you in anymore.<br><br><color orange>A Hero/Vigilante(or Villain/Rogue) who is in a Villain/Rogue(or Hero/Vigilante) Supergroup can not access any SG benefits such as bases, colors, or earning Prestige.  A character is not removed from the SG, so if they eventually return to their former alignment, they will be returned all supergroup privileges.</color>"
// Answer Text :
// Page SupergroupStatus Text :
"P644612619" "Okay, so let me tell you a story.  I worked for a dude a while ago.  He says to me, 'Yo! I'm going to the other side.  But get this - it's all part of my master plan.  In the meantime, I need you to keep an eye on the place until I get back.  Oh yeah, and I need you to fake my death.'  Yeah... I totally fell for that one.  Seriously?  He was gooooood. <br><br>The point is... if you're going to switch over, you better trick someone into taking over the role as leader BEFORE you switch, or you may get some dude running the show who you've never even heard of.<br><br>Don't be that guy.<br><br><color orange>When changes to your alignment prevent you from accessing your Supergroup, your rank will not be affected (such as date joined).  If you are the Leader of the SG (the Red Star), you will need to transfer leadership to another member before switching sides.  If you switch sides before transferring leadership, you will be demoted and another member will be randomly chosen to be the new SG leader.</color>"
// Answer Text :
// Page SupergroupTeams Text :
"P3218011124" "Look... you can team up with whoever you like, okay?  You may be some goody-two-shoes hero now, but some of your old partners in crime might still hang out with you... maybe not in public, though.  Or worse, though everyone may think you're the biggest heel that ever lived, you might have a friend here or there who knows that you're still working the biggest gig you've ever been given.  What sucks is when you're the last guy on the job and you've gotta make new friends to team with.<br><br>But a word of warning... don't EVER let 'em know who you are, got it?  It just... well, it just makes things easier while you're waiting.<br><br>By the way, I'm Pit.<br><br><color orange>A Rogue in a Hero/Vigilante Supergroup may join up with former teammates, even though they will not be able to enter Supergroup mode.  This also applies to Vigilantes in Villain/Rogue Supergroups.</color>"
// Answer Text :
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 

